Conquest.description: Creates a settlement.
Conquest.help: This command requires three arguments - settlement name (should be in quotes), settlement type (either *public* or *private) and entry fee (minimum 100)
Conquest.name: screate
Conquest.usage: This command requires three arguments - settlement name (should be in quotes), settlement type (either *public* or *private) and entry fee (minimum 100)

Conquest.description: Displays a settlement's public information.
Conquest.help: This command has one optional argument - the target individual. If no argument is parsed then the command will display the settlement you currectly reside in.
Conquest.name: sinfo
Conquest.usage: This command has one optional argument - the target individual. If no argument is parsed then the command will display the settlement you currectly reside in.

Conquest.description: Joins another individual's settlement
Conquest.help: This command requires two arguments - the settlement's invite code and entry fee (minimum the settlement's entry fee).
Conquest.name: join
Conquest.usage: This command requires two arguments - the settlement's invite code and entry fee (minimum the settlement's entry fee).

Conquest.description: Command to join a private settlement.
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: join private
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: Command to join a public settlement.
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: join public
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: A command group. If no subcommands are invoked by the user, this command will display your settlement's invide code.
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: code
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: Generates a new invite code for your settlement.
Conquest.help: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.
Conquest.name: code new
Conquest.usage: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.

Conquest.description: Displays your settlement's invite code. The code is sent privately to the author.
Conquest.help: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.
Conquest.name: code show
Conquest.usage: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.

Conquest.description: Attacks the target individual's settlement.
Conquest.help: Use it wisely!
Conquest.name: attack
Conquest.usage: Use it wisely!

Conquest.description: Returns the settlements' leaderboard
Conquest.help: This command takes one optional argument - the page number. If no argument is passed, then it defaults to 1.
Conquest.name: sleaderboard
Conquest.usage: This command takes one optional argument - the page number. If no argument is passed, then it defaults to 1.

Conquest.description: Leave the settlement you are currently in. (if any)
Conquest.help:
- Leaders of settlements with multiple residents cannot leave settlement without transferring ownership.
- Settlements with only one resident will get **DESTROYED** in the process!
Conquest.name: sleave
Conquest.usage:
- Leaders of settlements with multiple residents cannot leave settlement without transferring ownership.
- Settlements with only one resident will get **DESTROYED** in the process!

Conquest.description: Promotes the target individual to settlement leader.
Conquest.help: This command can **ONLY** be used by settlement leaders.
Conquest.name: promote
Conquest.usage: This command can **ONLY** be used by settlement leaders.

Conquest.description: Kicks the target individual from the settlement.
Conquest.help: This command can **ONLY** be used by settlement leaders.
Conquest.name: skick
Conquest.usage: This command can **ONLY** be used by settlement leaders.

Conquest.description: Displays the amount of resources currently stored in your settlement.
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: resources
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: A command group. If no subcommands are invoked by the user, this command will display the buildings' status of the settlement you are part of. (if any)
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: buildings
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: Displays the buildings' status of the settlement you are part of. (if any)
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: buildings list

Conquest.description: Displays the buildings' status of the settlement you are part of. (if any)

Conquest.name: buildings compact
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description:
Upgrades the target settlement building to the next level.
Buildings can be upgraded to Level 10.
Conquest.help: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.
Conquest.name: buildings upgrade
Conquest.usage: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.

Conquest.description: Displays target settlement building upgrade requirements for every level from 1 to 10.
Conquest.help: *Empty*
Conquest.name: requirements
Conquest.usage: *Empty*

Conquest.description: A command group. If no subcommands are invoked by the user, this command will display the resource market.
Conquest.help: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.
Conquest.name: market
Conquest.usage: This command can also be used directly in the bot's direct messages.

Conquest.description: Buys a set amount of resources from the market.
Conquest.help: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.
Conquest.name: market buy
Conquest.usage: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.

Conquest.description: Sells a set amount of resources on the market.
Conquest.help: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.
Conquest.name: market sell
Conquest.usage: This command can only be used by the leader of the settlement.

Conquest.description: Deposits a sum of money into the treasury of the settlement you are currently part of.
Conquest.help: You need to be part of a settlement to be able to use this command.
Conquest.name: deposit
Conquest.usage: You need to be part of a settlement to be able to use this command.

Conquest.description: Renames your settlement to the given name.
Conquest.help:
- You must be the leader of this settlement to be able to use this command.
- In order to rename your settlement, you need to pay a fee of 500 gold.
- Settlement names have a character limit of 50 characters.
Conquest.name: rename
Conquest.usage:
- You must be the leader of this settlement to be able to use this command.
- In order to rename your settlement, you need to pay a fee of 500 gold.
- Settlement names have a character limit of 50 characters.

Moderation.description: Deletes a set number of messages.
Moderation.help:
- This command requires a single argument - The number of messages you wish the bot to delete.
- Available filters: bot *(Filters are specified after the number of messages)*
Moderation.name: purge
Moderation.usage:
- This command requires a single argument - The number of messages you wish the bot to delete.
- Available filters: bot *(Filters are specified after the number of messages)*

Moderation.description: Kicks the mentioned individual for a certain reason (if any)
Moderation.help:
- The kick reason is an optional argument.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **kick** members.
Moderation.name: kick
Moderation.usage:
- The kick reason is an optional argument.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **kick** members.

Moderation.description: Bans the mentioned individual for a certain reason (if any)
Moderation.help:
- The ban reason is an optional argument.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **ban** members.
Moderation.name: ban
Moderation.usage:
- The ban reason is an optional argument.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **ban** members.

Moderation.description: Temporarily bans the mentioned invidivual for a specified amount of time for a certain reason (if any).
Moderation.help:
- This command accepts the following time units: `m(inutes), h(ours), d(ays), w(eeks)`
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **ban** members.
Moderation.name: tempban
Moderation.usage:
- This command accepts the following time units: `m(inutes), h(ours), d(ays), w(eeks)`
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **ban** members.

Moderation.description: Unbans the target individual from the server.
Moderation.help: Since the target individual can not be mentioned directly within the server, a <username>#<discriminator>(see example) or user ID should be provided.
Moderation.name: unban
Moderation.usage: Since the target individual can not be mentioned directly within the server, a <username>#<discriminator>(see example) or user ID should be provided.

Moderation.description: Soft bans the mentioned individual for a specified reason (if any)
Moderation.help:
- The soft ban reason is an optional argument.
- Soft bans in essence kick the target individual from the server while deleting their messages. It's not the same as a normal ban.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **kick** members and **manage** messages.
Moderation.name: softban
Moderation.usage:
- The soft ban reason is an optional argument.
- Soft bans in essence kick the target individual from the server while deleting their messages. It's not the same as a normal ban.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **kick** members and **manage** messages.

Moderation.description: Mutes the target individual from chatting on the server.
Moderation.help: *Empty*

Moderation.usage: *Empty*

Moderation.help:
- This command accepts the following time units: `m(inutes), h(ours), d(ays), w(eeks)`
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage messages**.

Moderation.usage:
- This command accepts the following time units: `m(inutes), h(ours), d(ays), w(eeks)`

Moderation.name: unmute

Moderation.description: Sets a chatting cooldown for the channel where the command was used.

- This command accepts the following time units: `s(econds), m(inutes), h(ours)`
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage messages** and **manage channels**.

Moderation.usage:
- This command accepts the following time units: `s(econds), m(inutes), h(ours)`

- A report reason must be provided in order to use this command.
- This command will only work when a report channel is set. (Disabled by default)

Moderation.usage: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Moderation.description: Enables server goodbye messages on the server.
Moderation.help: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.
Moderation.name: bye enable
Moderation.usage: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Moderation.description: Sets the text channel where greetings and goodbye messages are going to be sent by the bot.
Moderation.help:
- By default, these messages are sent to **#general**. If no text channel exists with that name, it uses the first text channel on the list.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.
Moderation.name: bye setchannel
Moderation.usage:
- By default, these messages are sent to **#general**. If no text channel exists with that name, it uses the first text channel on the list.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Moderation.description: Resets the greetings/goodbye messages text channel back to default.
Moderation.help:
- By default, these messages are sent to **#general**. If no text channel exists with that name, it uses the first text channel on the list.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.
Moderation.name: bye setchannel default
Moderation.usage:
- By default, these messages are sent to **#general**. If no text channel exists with that name, it uses the first text channel on the list.
- This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Moderation.description: Command to test your custom server goodbye message.
Moderation.help: This command can only be used by server **administrators**.
Moderation.name: bye test
Moderation.usage: This command can only be used by server **administrators**.

Moderation.description: Disables server goodbye messages on the server.
Moderation.help: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.
Moderation.name: bye disable
Moderation.usage: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Moderation.description: Changes the goodbye message to a custom one. Feel free to check the notes to be able to fully utilize this command.
Moderation.name: bye message

Moderation.description: Resets the server goodbye message back to default.
Moderation.help: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.
Moderation.name: bye message default
Moderation.usage: This command can only be used by users with the ability to **manage servers**.

Profiles.description: Displays the profile of the target user.
Profiles.help: If you do not specify a user, the bot will display your profile.
Profiles.name: profile
Profiles.usage: If you do not specify a user, the bot will display your profile.

Profiles.description: Sets (or resets) your profile's biography paragraph to the provided text.
Profiles.help: If you wish to reset your biography paragraph, provide no text to the command.
Profiles.name: bio
Profiles.usage: If you wish to reset your biography paragraph, provide no text to the command.

Profiles.description: Provides further information about all available profile backgrounds.
Profiles.help:
- Providing a number will display a preview of the profile background.
- Providing a category will display all available backgrounds within that category.
Profiles.name: background
Profiles.usage:
- Providing a number will display a preview of the profile background.
- Providing a category will display all available backgrounds within that category.

Profiles.description: Shows all profile backgrounds you currently own.
Profiles.help: Profile background purchases are global and can be used cross-server.
Profiles.name: background inventory
Profiles.usage: Profile background purchases are global and can be used cross-server.

Profiles.description: Changes your profile background back to default.
Profiles.name: background unequip

Profiles.description: Purchases a profile background from the shop for its' corresponding price
Profiles.help: All bought backgrounds are stored in your inventory and can be used cross-server. You only need to buy it once.
Profiles.name: background buy
Profiles.usage: All bought backgrounds are stored in your inventory and can be used cross-server. You only need to buy it once.

Profiles.description: Equips a profile background for the server where the command was executed.
Profiles.help: If you are not sure which profile backgrounds you own, you can view them by using one of the bot's commands to display your profile background inventory.
Profiles.name: background equip
Profiles.usage: If you are not sure which profile backgrounds you own, you can view them by using one of the bot's commands to display your profile background inventory.

Profiles.description: Toggles (enables/disables) experience gain and leveling on your server.
Profiles.help: This command can only be used by **server administrators**
Profiles.name: leveling
Profiles.usage: This command can only be used by **server administrators**

Profiles.description: Disables experience gain and leveling on your server.
Profiles.help: This command can only be used by **server administrators**
Profiles.name: leveling disable
Profiles.usage: This command can only be used by **server administrators**

Profiles.description: Resets experience and level progression for all users on your server back to 0.
Profiles.help: This command can only be used by **server owners**
Profiles.name: leveling reset
Profiles.usage: This command can only be used by **server owners**

Profiles.description: Enables experience gain and leveling on your server.
Profiles.help: This command can only be used by **server administrators**
Profiles.name: leveling enable
Profiles.usage: This command can only be used by **server administrators**

Utility.help: If no argument is parsed, the bot will instead return your avatar.
Utility.name: avatar
Utility.usage: If no argument is parsed, the bot will instead return your avatar.

Utility.description: Rolls a number in a given range.
Utility.help: If no argument is parsed, the bot will roll a number between 1 and 100.
Utility.name: roll
Utility.usage: If no argument is parsed, the bot will roll a number between 1 and 100.

Utility.description: Shows the target individual's user information.
Utility.help: If no argument is parsed, the bot will return your information instead.
Utility.name: userinfo
Utility.usage: If no argument is parsed, the bot will return your information instead.

Utility.description: Displays general information about the bot.
Utility.help: Server bot latency is directly tied to which shard the target server is placed in.
Utility.name: botinfo
Utility.usage: Server bot latency is directly tied to which shard the target server is placed in.

Utility.description: Returns an answer for a yes or no question.
Utility.name: 8ball

Utility.description: Picks a random item from a provided list of items, separated by a semicolon.
Utility.name: choose
